e, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, England":"Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Harcourt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and French: habitational name from any of the places in Eure and Calvados named Harcourt, from Old French <i>cour(t)</i> ‘court, farmyard’ (see   Court  ) with an obscure first element. This surname is very rare in France.","English: habitational name from either of two places in Shropshire named Harcourt. The one near Cleobury Mortimer gets the name from Old English <i>heafocere</i> ‘hawker, falconer’ + <i>cot</i> ‘hut, cottage’; the one near Wem has as its first element Old English <i>hearpere</i> (see   Harper  ).","History: The surname of French origin (see 1 above) is listed along with the equally rare or even extinct variants or altered forms <i>Haraucourt</i>, <i>Herancourt</i>, and <i>Héraucourt</i> in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."],"variants":[{"name":"Court","meanings":["English: topographic or occupational name from Middle English <i>curt</i>, <i>court</i> ‘large house’ (a word of the same ultimately Latin origin as 2 below), denoting someone who lived or worked in a manor house or castle, a courtly retainer.","French: topographic name from Old French <i>co(u)rt</i> ‘court, farmyard’ (from Latin <i>cohors</i>, <i>cors</i>, genitive <i>cohortis</i>, <i>cortis</i> ‘court, farmyard, enclosure’).","English and French: nickname for a physically small man, or ironically for a large man, from the adjective Middle English <i>curt</i>, Old French <i>co(u)rt</i> ‘short, small’ (from Latin <i>curtus</i> ‘curtailed, truncated, cut short, broken off’). Compare French   Lecourt  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John Harcourt was born in 1525, in Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 3 sons and 4 daughters with Lady Mary Maria Aston. He died in 1582, in Willingdon, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1525–1582":"1525–1582","1530–1610":"1530–1610","1538–Female":"1538–Surnud","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1542–Female":"1542–Surnud","1545–1618":"1545–1618","1549–1608":"1549–1608","1551–1608":"1551–1608","1577–1628":"1577–1628","Aft. 1540":"pärast 1540","1582":"1582","1525":"1525","about 1538":"umbes 1538","1545":"1545","1577":"1577","1610":"1610","1542":"1542","about 1545":"umbes 1545","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1540":"1540","1608":"1608","1618":"1618","1628":"1628","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Willingdon, Sussex, England":"Willingdon, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Messing, Essex, England":"Messing, Essex, England","of, Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, England":"Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chalgrove, Oxfordshire, England":"Chalgrove, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, England":"Stanton Harcourt, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1525–1582":"1525–1582","1530–1610":"1530–1610","1538–Female":"1538–Kuollut","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1542–Female":"1542–Kuollut","1545–1618":"1545–1618","1549–1608":"1549–1608","1551–1608":"1551–1608","1577–1628":"1577–1628","Aft. 1540":"1540 jälkeen","1582":"1582","1525":"1525","about 1538":"noin 1538","1545":"1545","1577":"1577","1610":"1610","1542":"1542","about 1545":"noin 1545","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1540":"1540","1608":"1608","1618":"1618","1628":"1628","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Ireland":"Irlanti","Willi